280.name: On A Sandy Beach near the Pier
desc: "   The land meets the sea here, forming a sandy beach.
The waves lap gently against the beach.  You can see
from here that at times the beach is gently sloped
but in the distance, sharp cliffs break the line
of golden sand.  A small pier with a few shacks
has been constructed just a little further along
the road.

710.name: A Pillar-Covered Hillside
desc: "   Small, white petaled flowers with bright, yellow centers
grow lazily from the path leading towards a stone staircase.
large, white platform at the top of the stairs.  Strange
vibrations are eminating from the stone collums, making them
appear as though they are breathing.  A light, flickering
from a golden object in the middle of the platform grabs
your attention.

711.name: A Strange Row Of Pillars
desc: "   Two gigantic stones stand steadfast in the hillside, gazing
over the stone platform.  You can barely fit between the stones,
since one has collapsed and leans towards the other.  White
ruins cover the walls from the top to the bottom.  A gigantic,
broken stone rests agains the collums directly behind them.
The stone is covered with the same runes as the other walls.  A
stone path leads back to the steps ascending to a stone platform
The sweet smell of flowers caress your nose as the wind passes
across the vast plains.

810.name: Under A Structure Of Stone
desc: "   A warm energy flows through you as you move closer to the
stone pillars.  Rune shaped writing covers the sides of the
giant stone collums.  The symbols glow with a solf, light blue
luminescence.  Looking up, the runes continue on the stone
ceiling above you.

811.name: The Altar of Seylaren-Li
desc: "   A white, circular platform lies atop the short row of
stairs.  Weeds and moss creep through the cracks of the six
large stones that make up the stone platform.  Small green
vines climb up a golden altar in the middle of the platform.
Writing, carefully scripted, completely covers the top of
the altar.  Elegant carvings of trees race around the sides
of the altar.  Golden carvings of cloaked archers appear to
race through the flourishing trees.
Carefully written in gold, you decipher, "Eith al kend,
En Seylaren-Li almana sentro."
